cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.LG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on speech processing and language acquisition research, which falls under the scope of this category. 
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper uses images as visual context to train the model, which is a key aspect of computer vision. 
3. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper deals with speech processing, which is a subfield of sound processing. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses neural models to map untranscribed speech to semantic keyword labels, which is a common technique in AI research. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses machine learning techniques to train the visually grounded speech model.
